The paper deals with game theoretic models of security games with multiple defenders, which falls under the category of computational game theory (cs.GT). It also involves analyzing security systems and networks, which could fall under the categories of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), systems and control (cs.SY), and networked systems (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper uses mixed-integer linear programming, which could fall under the category of optimization and control (cs.SI).
